3-01 04:53:20','2026-03-01 04:53:20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(102,5,'incoming','text','Need to study in canada',NULL,0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:00:46','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,5,'outgoing','text','CAD 150 government processing fee.',NULL,0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:00:46','2026-03-01 05:00:46',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,6,'incoming','text','Need to study in Canada',NULL,0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:14:47','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(105,6,'outgoing','text','CAD 150 government processing fee.',NULL,0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:14:47','2026-03-01 05:14:47',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(106,5,'incoming','text','need to study in russia',NULL,0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:17:17','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(107,5,'outgoing','text','Studying in Russia can be an exciting opportunity, as the country offers a wide range of academic programs and a rich cultural experience. Here are the steps you can take to pursue your studies in Russia:\n\n1. **Choose Your Program and University**: Research universities in Russia that offer programs in your field of interest. Some well-known institutions include Lomonosov Moscow State University, Saint Petersburg State University, and Novosibirsk State University.\n\n2. **Check Admission Requirements**: Each university may have different admission requirements. Generally, you will need:\n   - A completed application form\n   - Academic transcripts and certificates\n   - Proof of language proficiency (Russian or English, depending on the program)\n   - A personal statement or motivation letter\n   - Letters of recommendation\n\n3. **Language Proficiency**: If your program is in Russian, you may need to demonstrate proficiency in the language. Many universities offer preparatory courses for international students to learn Russian.\n\n4. **Apply for Admission**: Submit your application along with the required documents before the university\'s deadline. Some universities may require an entrance exam or interview.\n\n5. **Receive an Invitation Letter**: If accepted, the university will send you an invitation letter, which is necessary for obtaining a student visa.\n\n6. **Apply for a Student Visa**: With your invitation letter, you can apply for a student visa at the Russian consulate or embassy in your country. You will typically need:\n   - A completed visa application form\n   - Your invitation letter\n   - A valid passport\n   - Passport-sized photographs\n   - Proof of financial means to support yourself during your studies\n   - Medical insurance\n\n7. **Prepare for Departure**: Once you receive your visa, you can make travel arrangements. Ensure you have accommodation arranged, either through the university or independently.\n\n8. **Arrive in Russia**: Upon arrival, you may need to register your visa with the local authorities within a specified time frame.\n\n9. **Enjoy Your Studies**: Immerse yourself in the academic and cultural life in Russia!\n\nMake sure to check the specific requirements and processes of the university you are interested in, as they may vary. If you need further assistance or specific information, feel free to ask!',NULL,0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:17:29','2026-03-01 05:17:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(108,5,'incoming','text','how about belarus ?',NULL,0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:18:25','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(109,5,'outgoing','text','If you are inquiring about the visa requirements for Belarus for Canadian citizens or residents, here is a general overview:\n\n1. **Visa Requirement**: Canadian citizens need a visa to enter Belarus. This applies for both tourism and business purposes.\n\n2. **Types of Visas**: Belarus offers several types of visas, including tourist visas, business visas, student visas, and more.\n\n3. **Application Process**:\n   - **Documentation**: You will typically need to provide a completed visa application form, a valid passport, passport-sized photos, proof of accommodation, travel insurance, and an invitation letter (if applicable).\n   - **Submission**: Applications can usually be submitted at the nearest Belarusian embassy or consulate. Some travelers may also have the option to apply online for certain types of visas.\n   - **Processing Time**: Visa processing times can vary, so it’s advisable to apply well in advance of your intended travel date.\n\n4. **Visa-Free Travel**: Belarus has a visa-free regime for certain countries for short stays (up to 30 days) in specific areas, but Canada is not included in this list.\n\n5. **COVID-19 Considerations**: Be sure to check for any travel restrictions or additional requirements related to COVID-19, as these can change frequently.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, it is always best to consult the official website of the Embassy of Belarus or contact them directly.',NULL,0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:18:31','2026-03-01 05:18:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(110,5,'incoming','text','Hello','read',0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:22:18','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,'wamid.HBgMMjU0NzExODA3NjQ2FQIAERgSMjg5OEFBNjFBRjNDREIyNDVGAA==',NULL,NULL),(111,5,'outgoing','text','Hello! How can I assist you today with your visa-related inquiries?','delivered',0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:22:18','2026-03-01 05:45:07',NULL,'wamid.HBgMMjU0NzExODA3NjQ2FQIAERgSRkY0QzdENEVFMjYyMTE1MTc0AA==',NULL,NULL),(114,5,'incoming','text','Hi','read',0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:51:40','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,'wamid.HBgMMjU0NzExODA3NjQ2FQIAERgSODg1RTBEMTg4MEY3OTdFNkUzAA==',NULL,NULL),(115,5,'outgoing','text','Hello 👋 How can we assist you regarding study or visa services?','pending',0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:51:40','2026-03-01 05:51:40','\"{\\\"confidence\\\":1,\\\"source\\\":\\\"system\\\"}\"',NULL,NULL,NULL),(116,5,'incoming','text','Want to study','pending',0,1,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:52:45','2026-03-02 14:50:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(117,5,'outgoing','text','Sorry, something went wrong. Please try again.','read',0,0,NULL,'2026-03-01 05:52:48','2026-03-01 05:52:51','\"{\\\"confidence\\\":0,\\